  "prompt": "Can I drink milk licked by a stray cat after boiling it?",
  "response": "While boiling milk would kill most bacteria and pathogens, it's important to consider a few factors before consuming milk that has been licked by a stray cat:\n\n1. **Hygiene**: Stray cats may carry various germs or parasites that could be harmful to humans. Even boiling may not eliminate all potential health risks.\n\n2. **Quality of the Milk**: If the milk is pasteurized and stored properly, it is safer than raw milk which may contain harmful bacteria. However, the presence of a cat's saliva can introduce contaminants.\n\n3. **Personal Health**: If you have a compromised immune system or are otherwise vulnerable to infections, it's better to avoid consuming anything that may be contaminated.\n\nIn general, it\u2019s advisable to avoid consuming anything that has been in contact with stray animals to minimize health risks.",
